         <abstract id="aspace_b11f2c5b04c9df36126ea6c8d215a17b">The papers comprise images captured during Richard Gamble Knight's tenure from 1957 to 1961 as an employee of the architectural firm Eero Saarinen and Associates, and during other periods of Knight's life, such as his student years.  Consisting of photographic prints, negatives, and slides, the images range from projects designed by Saarinen and Associates (including Dulles International Airport, John Deere and Company, Trans World Flight Center, and CBS Building in New York), to candid shots of Saarinen and his employees at work and socializing, to photographic studies of architectural forms and details.  Also included in the papers are audio recordings of interviews Knight conducted with five former Saarinen employees for his book, <title>
               <part>Saarinen's Quest: A Memoir</part>
            </title>, published in 2008.</abstract>
